
[1]donation

   DONATION, n. [L., to give.]

   1. The act of giving or bestowing; a grant.

   That right we hold by his donation.

   2. In law, the act or contract by which a thing or the use of it is
   transferred to a person, or corporation, as a free gift. To be valid, a
   donation supposes capacity both in the donor to give and donee to take,
   and requires consent, acceptance and delivery.

   3. That which is given or bestowed; that which is transferred to
   another gratuitously, or without a valuable consideration; a gift; a
   grant. Donation is usually applied to things of more value than
   present.

   Mr. Boudinot made a donation of ten thousand dollars to the American
   Bible Society.
